@SG_CPP_CLASS SGWPageBackground
@SG_SHORT_DESCRP non scrollable background for @SG_FINDREP_WIDGET UI pages
@SG_LONG_DESCRP SGWPageBackground is used as the background for @SG_FINDREP_WIDGET UI pages as it works with SGWBackground::enable and SGWBackground::disable. It also blocks touch events, unlike SGWBlankWidget. If scrolling is desired, use either SGWScrollView or SGWSequentialScrollView. If blocking touch events is not necessary, use SGWBlankWidget instead.
@SG_IMPLE Stores information about the SGWPageBackground.
@SG_FUNC SGWPageBackground(SGWWidget* parent, float x1, float x0, float y1, float y0, float w1, float w0, float h1, float h0);
Creates a SGWPageBackground with parent @SG_FINDREP_WIDGET $parent and @SG_FINDREP_WDIST coordinates ($x1, $x0, $y1, $y0, $w1, $w0, $h1, $h0).
@SG_WARN $parent being nullptr is undefined behaviour.
@SG_WARN To avoid use after free bugs, deleting a SGWBackground directly will cause a crash. Use SGWBackground::disable or SGWWidget::deleteWidget to delete it safely.
